text: Canyon County is a county in the U.S. state of Idaho. As of the 2020 census, 231,105 people lived there, making it the second-most populous county in Idaho. The county seat is Caldwell, and largest city is Nampa. == Communities == === Cities === * Caldwell * Greenleaf * Melba * Middleton * Nampa * Notus * Parma * Star (partially) * Wilder === Unincorporated communities === * Bowmont * Huston * Riverside * Roswell * Sunnyslope == References == Category:1890s establishments in Idaho Category:1891 establishments in the United States Category:Idaho counties
title: Canyon County, Idaho
